      "title": "CDC reviewing eight projects, $490M in capital",
      "content": "<p></p><p>A Ã¢â‚¬Å“One Window ServiceÃ¢â‚¬Â meeting of the Cambodian Investment Board to examine and discuss investment project registration applications was held on the morning of April 21. The meeting was chaired by Chea Vuthy, CIB secretary-general, with participation from representatives of several government institutions, including subnational administrations.</p><p>According to the CDC, the eight projects have a combined capital of $490 million and are expected to create around 2,000 jobs. Among them, four projects fall under the industrial sector, including: a factory for manufacturing household electrical appliances; a factory producing inflatable mattresses, toys and swimming equipment; a yarn production and dyeing factory; and an expansion project adding garment washing operations to an existing garment and embroidery factory.</p>",
